Ondo Governor, Oluwarotimi Akeredolu, has abandoned his duties ahead of Monday’s primary of the All Progressives Congress(APC) to rush back over attack on worshippers in his country home. Akeredolu is Chairman, sub-committee on Security and Compliance for the APC presidential primary,   Buhari condemns terror attack on Ondo church     Four killed as cult groups clash in Bayelsa     Akeredolu urges Bello, Lawan to step down   A statement by his Chief Press Secretary, Richard Olatunde, said the Governor returned to Ondo State from the national assignment in Abuja. Olatunde said the Governor moved straight to Owo from the Akure Airport and received briefs from heads of security agencies in the State. “The Governor has vowed to hunt down the assailants and make them pay,” the statement reads.